author: newsroom@capegazette.com (Dan Cook)
title: Cape soccer presses to a 3-1 win over Caesar Rodney
text:
Cape soccer presses to a 3-1 win over Caesar Rodney By Dan Cook | Oct 22, 2015 Photo by: Dan Cook Senior forward Steven Matalavage scores the first goal of the contest off a pass from Zack Gelof. 
The Cape Soccer squad came out hot and put on the pressure to take a 3-1 win over the Riders Thursday, Oct. 22, at Legends Stadium. 
Senior Steven Matalavage started off the scoring with a goal at 5:00 into the game of a pass from Zack Gelof. Caesar Rodney followed with an own goal at 34:00. Drew Mulcahy tallied a goal at 54:00 off an assist from Gelof. 
Caesar Rodney got on the scoreboard at 79 minutes with a score from Thomas McPoyle off an assist from Chikezie Ikwuagwu . 
The Vikings out shot the Riders 17-7. Cape goalkeeper Brent Hochrein stopped six Rider shots. 
Cape 13-1 can win the Northern Division of the Henlopen Conference with a Tuesday October 27 home win over Dover. Brian Trupo and Steven Matalavage celebrate after the Caesar Rodney own goal in the first half of the 3-1 Viking victory. (Photo by: Dan Cook) The Viking squad celebrates Drew Mulcahy's goal in the second half of the 3-1 win. (Photo by: Dan Cook) Cape senior captain Jack Ashby collides with a CR defender in the midfield. (Photo by: Dan Cook) Senior center back Joao Ferreira, right, gets up for a high ball with Caesar Rodney's Chikezie Ikwuagwu. (Photo by: Dan Cook)
